<hr WIDTH="100%">

<h3>Lab Assignment:</h3>

Note: Everything in this lab assignment, unless otherwise stated, must be performed on the <span style="font-variant: small-caps;">csci2</span> server.

<ol TYPE=I>

    <li>
	Create the directory <code>lab6</code> in your <code>labs</code> directory, then move to it<br>
	(you can use the <code>cd</code> or <code>pushd</code> command in Unix to move to a directory).
    </li>

    <li>
    Perform LAB exercises <b>6.5</b> - <b>6.7</b> and LAB <b>6.8</b> <i>Options</i> <b>1</b> &amp; <b>2</b>.
    </li>

    <li>
	Use your editor to write the answers to the questions and exercises in
	<a href="http://web.stcloudstate.edu/aanda/cs201/Gaddis/7e/Labs/LM_Chapter06.2.pdf">Lab 6</a>
	in the file <code>Lab6answers.txt</code>
	locating it in directory <code>lab6</code></li>. Then submit the file to your lab6 dropbox in D2L.<br>
	As with all assignments submitted to a dropbox, your <u>name</u>, <u><span style="font-variant: small-caps;">csci2</span> login</u>, <u>assignment category</u> &amp; <u>number</u> [e.g. Lab 6],
	and <u>date</u> must be included at the top of your file.
    </li>

    <li>
    When you are sure that each program is working correctly, use the <code>script</code> command to display first the source file, then execution, 
    of each lab assignment program.  The <code><b>^D</b></code> character will end the <code>script</code> session.<br>
    What you enter into your <code>script</code> session will look like this:
    <code>
    <pre>
	&gt;script -a Lab6typescript.txt
	&gt;cat program1.cpp
	&gt;program1
	    (your input to program 1 is here)
	&gt;cat program1.cpp
	&gt;program2
	    (your input to program 2 is here)
	    .
	     .
	      .
	&gt;^D
    </pre>
    </code>
    Submit <code>Lab6typescript.txt</code> to the D2L Dropbox.
    </li>

</ol>
Here are the authors' source files for this lab:
<code>
    <ul>
	<li> <a href="http://web.stcloudstate.edu/aanda/cs201/Gaddis/7e/Labs/SourceCode/Lab6.2/scope.cpp">scope.cpp</a>
	<li> <a href="http://web.stcloudstate.edu/aanda/cs201/Gaddis/7e/Labs/SourceCode/Lab6.2/money.cpp">money.cpp</a>
	<li> <a href="http://web.stcloudstate.edu/aanda/cs201/Gaddis/7e/Labs/SourceCode/Lab6.2/convertmoney.cpp">convertmoney.cpp</a>
    </ul>
</code>


